129 MachineFunction &MF) { ----
130 MachineInstrBuilder MIB(MF, &MI); 0
131 if (!Subtarget->isABI_O32()) { // N32, N64 0
132 // Save current return address. ----

134 .addDef(Mips::AT_64) 0

140 // Save current return address. ----

142 .addDef(Mips::AT) 0

206 void MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectAddE(SDNode *Node, const SDLoc &DL) const { 0
207 SDValue InGlue = Node->getOperand(2); 0
208 unsigned Opc = InGlue.getOpcode(); 0
209 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0), RHS = Node->getOperand(1); 0
210 EVT VT = LHS.getValueType(); 0
211 ----
212 // In the base case, we can rely on the carry bit from the addsc ----
213 // instruction. ----
214 if (Opc == ISD::ADDC) { 0
215 SDValue Ops[3] = {LHS, RHS, InGlue}; 0
216 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(Node, Mips::ADDWC, VT, MVT::Glue, Ops); 0
217 return; 0
218 } ----
219 ----
220 assert(Opc == ISD::ADDE && "ISD::ADDE not in a chain of ADDE nodes!"); 0
221 ----
222 // The more complex case is when there is a chain of ISD::ADDE nodes like: ----
223 // (adde (adde (adde (addc a b) c) d) e). ----
224 // ----
225 // The addwc instruction does not write to the carry bit, instead it writes ----
226 // to bit 20 of the dsp control register. To match this series of nodes, each ----
227 // intermediate adde node must be expanded to write the carry bit before the ----
228 // addition. ----
229 ----
230 // Start by reading the overflow field for addsc and moving the value to the ----
231 // carry field. The usage of 1 here with MipsISD::RDDSP / Mips::WRDSP ----
232 // corresponds to reading/writing the entire control register to/from a GPR. ----
233 ----
234 SDValue CstOne = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
235 ----
236 SDValue OuFlag = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(20, DL, MVT::i32); 0
237 ----
238 SDNode *DSPCtrlField = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Mips::RDDSP, DL, MVT::i32, 0
239 MVT::Glue, CstOne, InGlue); ----
240 ----
241 SDNode *Carry = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
242 Mips::EXT, DL, MVT::i32, SDValue(DSPCtrlField, 0), OuFlag, CstOne); ----
243 ----
244 SDValue Ops[4] = {SDValue(DSPCtrlField, 0), ----
245 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(6, DL, MVT::i32), CstOne, 0
246 SDValue(Carry, 0)}; 0
247 SDNode *DSPCFWithCarry = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Mips::INS, DL, MVT::i32, Ops); 0
248 ----
249 // My reading of the MIPS DSP 3.01 specification isn't as clear as I ----
250 // would like about whether bit 20 always gets overwritten by addwc. ----
251 // Hence take an extremely conservative view and presume it's sticky. We ----
252 // therefore need to clear it. ----
253 ----
254 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getRegister(Mips::ZERO, MVT::i32); 0
255 ----
256 SDValue InsOps[4] = {Zero, OuFlag, CstOne, SDValue(DSPCFWithCarry, 0)}; 0
257 SDNode *DSPCtrlFinal = ----
258 CurDAG->getMachineNode(Mips::INS, DL, MVT::i32, InsOps); 0
259 ----
260 SDNode *WrDSP = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Mips::WRDSP, DL, MVT::Glue, 0
261 SDValue(DSPCtrlFinal, 0), CstOne); ----
262 ----
263 SDValue Operands[3] = {LHS, RHS, SDValue(WrDSP, 0)}; 0
264 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(Node, Mips::ADDWC, VT, MVT::Glue, Operands); 0
265 } ----

533 ----
534 // Select constant vector splats. ----
535 // ----
536 // In addition to the requirements of selectVSplat(), this function returns ----
537 // true and sets Imm if: ----
538 // * The splat value is the same width as the elements of the vector ----
539 // * The splat value fits in an integer with the specified signed-ness and ----
540 // width. ----
541 // ----
542 // This function looks through ISD::BITCAST nodes. ----
543 // TODO: This might not be appropriate for big-endian MSA since BITCAST is ----
544 // sometimes a shuffle in big-endian mode. ----
545 // ----
546 // It's worth noting that this function is not used as part of the selection ----
547 // of ldi.[bhwd] since it does not permit using the wrong-typed ldi.[bhwd] ----
548 // instruction to achieve the desired bit pattern. ldi.[bhwd] is selected in ----
549 // MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectNode. ----
550 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel:: 0
551 selectVSplatCommon(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm, bool Signed, ----
552 unsigned ImmBitSize) const { ----
553 APInt ImmValue; 0
554 EVT EltTy = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(); 0
555 ----
556 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) 0
557 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
558 ----
559 if (selectVSplat(N.getNode(), ImmValue, EltTy.getSizeInBits()) && 0
560 ImmValue.getBitWidth() == EltTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
561 ----
562 if (( Signed && ImmValue.isSignedIntN(ImmBitSize)) || 0
563 (!Signed && ImmValue.isIntN(ImmBitSize))) { 0
564 Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmValue, SDLoc(N), EltTy); 0
565 return true; 0
566 } ----
567 } ----
568 ----
569 return false; 0
570 } 0
571 ----
572 // Select constant vector splats. ----
573 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel:: 0
574 selectVSplatUimm1(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) const { ----
575 return selectVSplatCommon(N, Imm, false, 1); 0
576 } ----
577 ----
578 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel:: 0
579 selectVSplatUimm2(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) const { ----
580 return selectVSplatCommon(N, Imm, false, 2); 0
581 } ----
582 ----
583 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel:: 0
584 selectVSplatUimm3(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) const { ----
585 return selectVSplatCommon(N, Imm, false, 3); 0
586 } ----

618 // Select constant vector splats whose value is a power of 2. ----
619 // ----
620 // In addition to the requirements of selectVSplat(), this function returns ----
621 // true and sets Imm if: ----
622 // * The splat value is the same width as the elements of the vector ----
623 // * The splat value is a power of two. ----
624 // ----
625 // This function looks through ISD::BITCAST nodes. ----
626 // TODO: This might not be appropriate for big-endian MSA since BITCAST is ----
627 // sometimes a shuffle in big-endian mode. ----
628 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatUimmPow2(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) const { 0
629 APInt ImmValue; 0
630 EVT EltTy = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(); 0
631 ----
632 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) 0
633 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
634 ----
635 if (selectVSplat(N.getNode(), ImmValue, EltTy.getSizeInBits()) && 0
636 ImmValue.getBitWidth() == EltTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
637 int32_t Log2 = ImmValue.exactLogBase2(); 0
638 ----
639 if (Log2 != -1) { 0
640 Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Log2, SDLoc(N), EltTy); 0
641 return true; 0
642 } ----
643 } ----
644 ----
645 return false; 0
646 } 0
647 ----
648 // Select constant vector splats whose value only has a consecutive sequence ----
649 // of left-most bits set (e.g. 0b11...1100...00). ----
650 // ----
651 // In addition to the requirements of selectVSplat(), this function returns ----
652 // true and sets Imm if: ----
653 // * The splat value is the same width as the elements of the vector ----
654 // * The splat value is a consecutive sequence of left-most bits. ----
655 // ----
656 // This function looks through ISD::BITCAST nodes. ----
657 // TODO: This might not be appropriate for big-endian MSA since BITCAST is ----
658 // sometimes a shuffle in big-endian mode. ----
659 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatMaskL(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) const { 0
660 APInt ImmValue; 0
661 EVT EltTy = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(); 0
662 ----
663 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) 0
664 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
665 ----
666 if (selectVSplat(N.getNode(), ImmValue, EltTy.getSizeInBits()) && 0
667 ImmValue.getBitWidth() == EltTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
668 // Extract the run of set bits starting with bit zero from the bitwise ----
669 // inverse of ImmValue, and test that the inverse of this is the same ----
670 // as the original value. ----
671 if (ImmValue == ~(~ImmValue & ~(~ImmValue + 1))) { 0
672 ----
673 Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmValue.popcount() - 1, SDLoc(N), EltTy); 0
674 return true; 0
675 } ----
676 } ----
677 ----
678 return false; 0
679 } 0
680 ----
681 // Select constant vector splats whose value only has a consecutive sequence ----
682 // of right-most bits set (e.g. 0b00...0011...11). ----
683 // ----
684 // In addition to the requirements of selectVSplat(), this function returns ----
685 // true and sets Imm if: ----
686 // * The splat value is the same width as the elements of the vector ----
687 // * The splat value is a consecutive sequence of right-most bits. ----
688 // ----
689 // This function looks through ISD::BITCAST nodes. ----
690 // TODO: This might not be appropriate for big-endian MSA since BITCAST is ----
691 // sometimes a shuffle in big-endian mode. ----
692 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatMaskR(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) const { 0
693 APInt ImmValue; 0
694 EVT EltTy = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(); 0
695 ----
696 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) 0
697 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
698 ----
699 if (selectVSplat(N.getNode(), ImmValue, EltTy.getSizeInBits()) && 0
700 ImmValue.getBitWidth() == EltTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
701 // Extract the run of set bits starting with bit zero, and test that the ----
702 // result is the same as the original value ----
703 if (ImmValue == (ImmValue & ~(ImmValue + 1))) { 0
704 Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmValue.popcount() - 1, SDLoc(N), EltTy); 0
705 return true; 0
706 } ----
707 } ----
708 ----
709 return false; 0
710 } 0
711 ----
712 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatUimmInvPow2(SDValue N, 0
713 SDValue &Imm) const { ----
714 APInt ImmValue; 0
715 EVT EltTy = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(); 0
716 ----
717 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) 0
718 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
719 ----
720 if (selectVSplat(N.getNode(), ImmValue, EltTy.getSizeInBits()) && 0
721 ImmValue.getBitWidth() == EltTy.getSizeInBits()) { 0
722 int32_t Log2 = (~ImmValue).exactLogBase2(); 0
723 ----
724 if (Log2 != -1) { 0
725 Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Log2, SDLoc(N), EltTy); 0
726 return true; 0
727 } ----
728 } ----
729 ----
730 return false; 0
731 } 0

988 ----
989 // Manually match MipsISD::Ins nodes to get the correct instruction. It has ----
990 // to be done in this fashion so that we respect the differences between ----
991 // dins and dinsm, as the difference is that the size operand has the range ----
992 // 0 < size <= 32 for dins while dinsm has the range 2 <= size <= 64 which ----
993 // means SelectionDAGISel would have to test all the operands at once to ----
994 // match the instruction. ----
995 case MipsISD::Ins: { 0
996 ----
997 // Validating the node operands. ----
998 if (Node->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32 && Node->getValueType(0) != MVT::i64) 0
999 return false; 0
1000 ----
1001 if (Node->getNumOperands() != 4) 0
1002 return false; 0
1003 ----
1004 if (Node->getOperand(1)->getOpcode() != ISD::Constant || 0
1005 Node->getOperand(2)->getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) 0
1006 return false; 0
1007 ----
1008 MVT ResTy = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
1009 uint64_t Pos = Node->getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
1010 uint64_t Size = Node->getConstantOperandVal(2); 0
1011 ----
1012 // Size has to be >0 for 'ins', 'dins' and 'dinsu'. ----
1013 if (!Size) 0
1014 return false; 0
1015 ----
1016 if (Pos + Size > 64) 0
1017 return false; 0
1018 ----
1019 if (ResTy != MVT::i32 && ResTy != MVT::i64) 0
1020 return false; 0
1021 ----
1022 unsigned Opcode = 0; 0
1023 if (ResTy == MVT::i32) { 0
1024 if (Pos + Size <= 32) 0
1025 Opcode = Mips::INS; 0
1026 } else { ----
1027 if (Pos + Size <= 32) 0
1028 Opcode = Mips::DINS; 0
1029 else if (Pos < 32 && 1 < Size) 0
1030 Opcode = Mips::DINSM; 0
1031 else ----
1032 Opcode = Mips::DINSU; 0
1033 } ----
1034 ----
1035 if (Opcode) { 0
1036 SDValue Ops[4] = { ----
1037 Node->getOperand(0), CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Pos, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1038 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Size, DL, MVT::i32), Node->getOperand(3)}; 0
1039 ----
1040 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, ResTy, Ops)); 0
1041 return true; 0
1042 } ----
1043 ----
1044 return false; 0
1045 } ----
1046 ----
1047 case MipsISD::ThreadPointer: { 0
1048 EVT PtrVT = getTargetLowering()->getPointerTy(CurDAG->getDataLayout()); 0
1049 unsigned RdhwrOpc, DestReg; ----
1050 ----
1051 if (PtrVT == MVT::i32) { 0
1052 RdhwrOpc = Mips::RDHWR; 0
1053 DestReg = Mips::V1; 0
1054 } else { ----
1055 RdhwrOpc = Mips::RDHWR64; 0
1056 DestReg = Mips::V1_64; 0
1057 } ----
1058 ----
1059 SDNode *Rdhwr = ----
1060 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RdhwrOpc, DL, Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Glue, 0
1061 CurDAG->getRegister(Mips::HWR29, MVT::i32), 0
1062 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1063 SDValue Chain = CurDAG->getCopyToReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, DestReg, 0
1064 SDValue(Rdhwr, 0), SDValue(Rdhwr, 1)); ----
1065 SDValue ResNode = CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, DestReg, PtrVT, 0
1066 Chain.getValue(1)); ----
1067 ReplaceNode(Node, ResNode.getNode()); 0
1068 return true; 0
1069 } ----
1070 ----
1071 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: { 0
1072 // Select appropriate ldi.[bhwd] instructions for constant splats of ----
1073 // 128-bit when MSA is enabled. Fixup any register class mismatches that ----
1074 // occur as a result. ----
1075 // ----
1076 // This allows the compiler to use a wider range of immediates than would ----
1077 // otherwise be allowed. If, for example, v4i32 could only use ldi.h then ----
1078 // it would not be possible to load { 0x01010101, 0x01010101, 0x01010101, ----
1079 // 0x01010101 } without using a constant pool. This would be sub-optimal ----
1080 // when // 'ldi.b wd, 1' is capable of producing that bit-pattern in the ----
1081 // same set/ of registers. Similarly, ldi.h isn't capable of producing { ----
1082 // 0x00000000, 0x00000001, 0x00000000, 0x00000001 } but 'ldi.d wd, 1' can. ----
1083 ----
1084 const MipsABIInfo &ABI = ----
1085 static_cast(TM).getABI(); 0
1086 ----
1087 BuildVectorSDNode *BVN = cast(Node); 0
1088 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef; 0
1089 unsigned SplatBitSize; ----
1090 bool HasAnyUndefs; ----
1091 unsigned LdiOp; ----
1092 EVT ResVecTy = BVN->getValueType(0); 0
1093 EVT ViaVecTy; 0
1094 ----
1095 if (!Subtarget->hasMSA() || !BVN->getValueType(0).is128BitVector()) 0
1096 return false; 0
1097 ----
1098 if (!BVN->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, 0
1099 HasAnyUndefs, 8, ----
1100 !Subtarget->isLittle())) 0
1101 return false; 0
1102 ----
1103 switch (SplatBitSize) { 0
1104 default: 0
1105 return false; 0
1106 case 8: 0
1107 LdiOp = Mips::LDI_B; 0
1108 ViaVecTy = MVT::v16i8; 0
1109 break; 0
1110 case 16: 0
1111 LdiOp = Mips::LDI_H; 0
1112 ViaVecTy = MVT::v8i16; 0
1113 break; 0
1114 case 32: 0
1115 LdiOp = Mips::LDI_W; 0
1116 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32; 0
1117 break; 0
1118 case 64: 0
1119 LdiOp = Mips::LDI_D; 0

1153 : (SplatBitSize == 64 ? Mips::FILL_D : 0)); 0

1155 assert(FILLOp != 0 && "Unknown FILL Op for splat synthesis!"); 0

1215 // If we have a 64 bit Splat value, we perform a similar sequence to the ----
1216 // above: ----
1217 // ----
1218 // MIPS32: MIPS64: ----
1219 // lui $res, %highest(val) lui $res, %highest(val) ----
1220 // ori $res, $res, %higher(val) ori $res, $res, %higher(val) ----
1221 // lui $res2, %hi(val) lui $res2, %hi(val) ----
1222 // ori $res2, %res2, %lo(val) ori $res2, %res2, %lo(val) ----
1223 // $res3 = fill $res2 dinsu $res, $res2, 0, 32 ----
1224 // $res4 = insert.w $res3[1], $res fill.d $res ----
1225 // splat.d $res4, 0 ----
1226 // ----
1227 // The ability to use dinsu is guaranteed as MSA requires MIPSR5. ----
1228 // This saves having to materialize the value by shifts and ors. ----
1229 // ----

1234 // daui $res, $res, %hi(val) ----

1238 // ----

1248 SDValue HighestVal = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Highest, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1249 SDValue ZeroVal = CurDAG->getRegister(Mips::ZERO, MVT::i32); 0
1250 ----
1251 // Independent of whether we're targeting MIPS64 or not, the basic ----
1252 // operations are the same. Also, directly use the $zero register if ----
1253 // the 16 bit chunk is zero. ----
1254 // ----
1255 // For optimization purposes we always synthesize the splat value as ----
1256 // an i32 value, then if we're targetting MIPS64, use SUBREG_TO_REG ----
1257 // just before combining the values with dinsu to produce an i64. This ----
1258 // enables SelectionDAG to aggressively share components of splat values ----
1259 // where possible. ----
1260 // ----

1282 ----
1283 ----
1284 if (ABI.IsO32()) { 0

1286 (Hi || Lo) ? SDValue(Res, 0) : ZeroVal); 0

1291 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0

1300 ----
1301 Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1302 Mips::SPLATI_D, DL, MVT::v2i64, SDValue(Res, 0), ----
1303 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0

1305 ----
1306 SDValue Zero64Val = CurDAG->getRegister(Mips::ZERO_64, MVT::i64); 0

1380 bool MipsSEDAGToDAGISel:: 0
1381 SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperand(const SDValue &Op, unsigned ConstraintID, ----
1382 std::vector &OutOps) { ----
1383 SDValue Base, Offset; 0
1384 ----
1385 switch(ConstraintID) { 0
1386 default: 0
1387 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected asm memory constraint"); 0
1388 // All memory constraints can at least accept raw pointers. ----
1389 case InlineAsm::Constraint_m: 0
1390 case InlineAsm::Constraint_o: ----
1391 if (selectAddrRegImm16(Op, Base, Offset)) { 0
1392 OutOps.push_back(Base); 0
1393 OutOps.push_back(Offset); 0
1394 return false; 0
1395 } ----
1396 OutOps.push_back(Op); 0
1397 OutOps.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), MVT::i32)); 0
1398 return false; 0
1399 case InlineAsm::Constraint_R: 0
1400 // The 'R' constraint is supposed to be much more complicated than this. ----
1401 // However, it's becoming less useful due to architectural changes and ----
1402 // ought to be replaced by other constraints such as 'ZC'. ----
1403 // For now, support 9-bit signed offsets which is supportable by all ----
1404 // subtargets for all instructions. ----
1405 if (selectAddrRegImm9(Op, Base, Offset)) { 0
1406 OutOps.push_back(Base); 0
1407 OutOps.push_back(Offset); 0
1408 return false; 0
1409 } ----
1410 OutOps.push_back(Op); 0
1411 OutOps.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), MVT::i32)); 0
1412 return false; 0
1413 case InlineAsm::Constraint_ZC: 0
1414 // ZC matches whatever the pref, ll, and sc instructions can handle for the ----
1415 // given subtarget. ----
1416 if (Subtarget->inMicroMipsMode()) { 0
1417 // On microMIPS, they can handle 12-bit offsets. ----
1418 if (selectAddrRegImm12(Op, Base, Offset)) { 0
1419 OutOps.push_back(Base); 0
1420 OutOps.push_back(Offset); 0
1421 return false; 0
1422 } ----
1423 } else if (Subtarget->hasMips32r6()) { 0
1424 // On MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6, they can only handle 9-bit offsets. ----
1425 if (selectAddrRegImm9(Op, Base, Offset)) { 0
1426 OutOps.push_back(Base); 0
1427 OutOps.push_back(Offset); 0
1428 return false; 0
1429 } ----
1430 } else if (selectAddrRegImm16(Op, Base, Offset)) { 0
1431 // Prior to MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6, they can handle 16-bit offsets. ----
1432 OutOps.push_back(Base); 0
1433 OutOps.push_back(Offset); 0
1434 return false; 0
1435 } ----
1436 // In all cases, 0-bit offsets are acceptable. ----
1437 OutOps.push_back(Op); 0
1438 OutOps.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), MVT::i32)); 0
1439 return false; 0
1440 } ----
1441 return true; ----
1442 } ----

223 // (adde (adde (adde (addc a b) c) d) e). 223 // (adde (adde (adde (addc a b) c) d) e).
